s the picture that astronomical PAHs are large with compact, regular\nstructures. From the coupling with primarily strong CH out-of-plane bending\nmodes one might surmise that the 5.25 and 5.7 $\\mu$m bands track the neutral\nPAH population. However, theory suggests the role of charge in these\nastronomical bands might also be important.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 9 Sep 2008 17:46:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2011-02-11"}
