27.4 had spectroscopic characteristics which were very different\nbetween the SDSS spectrum and our own VLT observations, despite only a small\nchange in brightness. We measure Porb = 98.012 +/- 0.065 min from its narrow\nHalpha emission line. Finally, SDSS J223843.84+010820.7 has a comparatively\nlonger period of Porb = 194.30 +/- 0.16 min. It contains a magnetic white dwarf\nand, with g = 18.15, is brighter than the other objects studied here. These\nresults continue the trend for the fainter CVs identified by the SDSS to be\nalmost exclusively shorter-period objects with low mass transfer rates.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 10 Sep 2008 10:21:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
